  <h2>Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    At LocalPDF, your privacy is not just a feature—it's our core architecture. Unlike traditional online
    PDF services that upload your files to remote servers, LocalPDF processes everything locally in your
    browser. This means we literally cannot access, view, store, or share your documents.
  </p>

  <p><strong>TL;DR:</strong> We don't collect your data because we never see it.</p>

  <h2>What Data We Collect</h2>
  <p><strong>None.</strong></p>

  <p>
    LocalPDF does not collect, process, store, or transmit any of the following:
  </p>

  <ul>
    <li>PDF files or documents you upload</li>
    <li>Personal information (names, emails, addresses)</li>
    <li>IP addresses or device identifiers</li>
    <li>Browser fingerprints or usage analytics</li>
    <li>Cookies (we don't use any cookies)</li>
    <li>Session data or browsing history</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="info-box">
    <strong>Technical Explanation:</strong> When you upload a PDF to LocalPDF, the file is loaded directly
    into your browser's JavaScript runtime memory. All processing (merging, splitting, compressing, etc.)
    happens using client-side libraries (pdf-lib, PDF.js, Tesseract.js). There are zero network requests
    to our servers during processing. When you download the result, it's generated in your browser and
    saved to your device via the browser's native download API.
  </div>

  <h2>How LocalPDF Works (Privacy Perspective)</h2>

  <h3>1. File Upload</h3>
  <p>
    When you select a PDF file using our file picker, the browser reads the file from your local disk
    into memory. This happens entirely within your browser—no network transmission occurs.
  </p>

  <h3>2. Processing</h3>
  <p>
    All PDF manipulation happens in your browser using JavaScript and WebAssembly. The pdf-lib library
    (for merging, splitting, etc.) and PDF.js (for rendering) run locally. Your files never leave your
    device's RAM.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Download</h3>
  <p>
    When processing is complete, the modified PDF is generated in your browser's memory and offered as
    a download using the browser's built-in download mechanism. We don't intercept or store this file.
  </p>

  <h3>4. Cleanup</h3>
  <p>
    Once you close the browser tab or navigate away, all file data is automatically cleared from memory.
    There's no server-side storage, no backups, no "trash" folder.
  </p>

  <h2>GDPR Compliance (EU Regulation 2016/679)</h2>

  <p>
    LocalPDF is fully compliant with the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) by design. Here's how
    we address each key GDPR principle:
  </p>

  <h3>1. Lawfulness, Fairness, and Transparency (Article 5.1.a)</h3>
  <p>
    Since we don't process personal data, we don't require a legal basis (consent, contract, legitimate
    interest, etc.) for data processing. Our service is transparent: what you see is what you get—100%
    client-side processing.
  </p>

  <h3>2. Purpose Limitation (Article 5.1.b)</h3>
  <p>
    Not applicable—we don't collect data, so there's no purpose to limit.
  </p>

  <h3>3. Data Minimization (Article 5.1.c)</h3>
  <p>
    We've minimized data collection to zero. You can't get more minimal than that.
  </p>

  <h3>4. Accuracy (Article 5.1.d)</h3>
  <p>
    Not applicable—we don't store data, so there's no data to keep accurate.
  </p>

  <h3>5. Storage Limitation (Article 5.1.e)</h3>
  <p>
    Data is stored only in your browser's temporary memory during active use. When you close the tab,
    it's erased. Storage duration: seconds to minutes, never longer.
  </p>

  <h3>6. Integrity and Confidentiality (Article 5.1.f)</h3>
  <p>
    Your data never leaves your device, so there's no risk of data breaches, unauthorized access, or
    interception. This is the highest level of confidentiality possible.
  </p>

