  <h2>Third-Party Services</h2>

  <h3>Hosting</h3>
  <p>
    LocalPDF is hosted on standard web hosting infrastructure. When you load our website, your browser
    makes a standard HTTP request to retrieve static files (HTML, CSS, JavaScript). This is a normal
    web request and may be logged by our hosting provider (e.g., IP address, timestamp, user agent).
    However, these logs do not contain any PDF files or document content.
  </p>

  <h3>Fonts</h3>
  <p>
    We load the Inter font from Google Fonts. When your browser loads our site, it may request font
    files from Google's CDN. This is a standard resource request and does not involve transmitting
    your PDF files. You can read Google Fonts' privacy policy
    <a href="https://developers.google.com/fonts/faq#what_does_using_the_google_fonts_api_mean_for_the_privacy_of_my_users" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>

  <h3>Analytics</h3>
  <p>
    <strong>We do not use Google Analytics, Facebook Pixel, or any third-party tracking scripts.</strong>
    There are no cookies, no fingerprinting, no session recording.
  </p>

  <h2>Data Breaches</h2>
  <p>
    Since we don't collect, store, or transmit your personal data, there's nothing for us to breach.
    If a malicious actor gained access to our servers, they would find zero user data—no PDFs, no
    personal information, nothing.
  </p>

  <p>
    The only theoretical risk is browser-level vulnerabilities (e.g., malicious browser extensions
    reading your local memory). This is outside our control and applies to all web applications.
  </p>

  <h2>International Data Transfers</h2>
  <p>
    Not applicable. Your data never leaves your device, so there are no cross-border transfers.
    You could be in Europe, Asia, or Antarctica—your PDFs stay local.
  </p>

  <h2>Children's Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    LocalPDF does not collect personal data from anyone, including children under 13 (COPPA) or 16 (GDPR).
    Since we don't collect data, we don't need parental consent.
  </p>

  <h2>Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    If we ever change our privacy practices (unlikely, given our zero-data architecture), we'll update
    this page and change the "Last Updated" date above. Significant changes will be announced on our
    homepage.
  </p>

  <h2>Contact &amp; Data Protection Officer</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy-related questions, contact us at:
    <br><strong>Email:</strong> <a href="mailto:privacy@localpdf.online">privacy@localpdf.online</a>
  </p>

  <p>
    Since we don't process personal data, we're not required to appoint a Data Protection Officer (DPO)
    under GDPR Article 37. However, if you have concerns about GDPR compliance, feel free to reach out.
  </p>

  <h2>Supervisory Authority</h2>
  <p>
    If you're in the EU and believe we're violating GDPR (though we're not sure how, given we don't
    collect data), you have the right to lodge a complaint with your local data protection authority.
    Find your authority <a href="https://edpb.europa.eu/about-edpb/board/members_en" target="_blank">here</a>.
  </p>

